                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d524">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">352.1121 Blodgett, Walton/134: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain (<persName type="from"
                            >Bowers</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-27T10:00:00+00:00"
                            >October 27, 1933—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 27—7:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>65. My telegram No. 64.<note n="47" xml:id="d524fn47">Dated October 25, not
                        printed; it indicated that the trial of the five Americans would take place
                        October 26th.</note> Following from Dawson at Palma de Mallorca: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Acquittal all five subject to review.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
